# Inventory Manager Mobile API

## Overview

This document is the current mobile contract for the `inventory_manager` role.
It is based on the live Laravel API and replaces earlier notes that treated purchase as simple-product only.

For a focused Flutter implementation guide for add-product, barcode scan, and variant product create/edit, see:

- [docs/inventory_manager_mobile_product_add_flow.md](/Users/fazlerabbi/Desktop/Projects/tonmoy/inventory_management_system_tnmy/docs/inventory_manager_mobile_product_add_flow.md)

Current inventory-manager mobile scope:

- authentication
- master data preload
- product list and detail
- manual product create/update
- barcode-driven product create/update
- purchase list/detail
- purchase create/update
- purchase barcode lookup

Default protected header for production:

```http
Accept: application/json
X-Authorization: Bearer {token}
```

Use standard `Authorization: Bearer {token}` only if your target environment passes it through correctly.

